column11: The data you carry is vital to the remaining Federation fleet. You'll need supplies for the journey, so make sure to explore each sector before moving on to the next. But get to the exit before the pursuing Rebel fleet can catch up!  TIP: Fire -  If fire is spreading, consider opening airlocks and doors to vent the oxygen from parts of your ship. Fire is quickly extinguished without O2.

You locate the highest concentration of life forms and bring the ship alongside the station. Before you can begin to offload the survivors, a huge blast splits the station apart. Your ship is thrown away and some debris pierces your hull. You watch helplessly as the last of the survivors are consumed in the collapse of the station.
Your jump leads to a completely unremarkable binary star system. There is nothing else around.
Their ship breaks apart and you are relieved to know that you are still one step ahead of the fleet.
You access the recent scans from the unguarded station. Your map has been updated with details of the surrounding area.
Scans reveal a number of asteroids with useful compositions. You extract some fuel.
The ship breaks apart and you feel relief in the knowledge that you will hopefully still be one step ahead of the fleet.
The space station here has a traveling merchant who shows you his wares.
column12: Weapon: LASER CHARGEGUN 2, BEAM 2, LASER HEAVY 1, Crew: Rock, Rock, Engi, Drone: DEFENSE 1, ANTI DRONE, REPAIR,

column11: The outpost hails you, The pompous bastards expected free service just because they defeated the Federation. Take this for the help.
I understand. Good luck out there. We'll try to make do with what we have.
Once the Federation forces were scattered, the Rebels came down hard on the locals here. Between the 'tax collectors' and military bases, the Rebel presence in this sector is high.

You enter a system bustling with Rebel activity. Supply freighters and re-supply stations are dwarfed by a few heavy warships. Luckily, no one seems to be paying attention to small cruisers. No ships are scanning or messaging you.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

There appear to be a number of small stations nearby. Before you have time to scan them, warnings go off. A Rebel teleporter was used in one of the stations. You've been boarded! They must have a Super Shield bypass unit; boarders are on board!
The station was apparently designed to outfit Rebel ships with Drone Systems. You find a functioning Schematic.
The ship breaks apart and you feel relief in the knowledge that you will hopefully still be one step ahead of the fleet.

You arrive near a small Rebel refueling depot. Your ship is being scanned multiple times so they must recognize you, but there appears to be no combat-ready ships in the vicinity. The only message you receive is a denial to your request to dock at the depot.
Their ship breaks apart and you are relieved to know that you are still one step ahead of the fleet.
Take this bit of scrap as a down-payment. We'll use your jump signatures to follow you. You're really helping us out here. Added a quest marker to the next sector!
You receive generic advertisements from a nearby public ship-yard. It seems they are willing to work on any ship, not only those of Rebel hue.

column11: The station was either abandoned or stripped clean. It seems to have lain unused for quite some time. You find nothing useful.
Thank you for your business.
Welcome to a new sector! Get to the exit beacon and jump to the next sector before the pursuing Rebels catch you!
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

The space station here has a traveling merchant who shows you his wares.

column11: Good choice, son. We've both come out of this richer.
You cycle through wide-band comm channels as soon as you arrive. Nothing but static.
The ship you were escorting thanks you, I don't think we could have made it without your help. Let my friends patch up some of your hull and show you their wares.
column12: System: medbay, teleporter, mind, Weapon: BOMB 1, ION 1, LASER BURST 3, Drone: BATTLE, COMBAT 1, REPAIR,

column11: You try your best but one stray rock hits a key structure in their ship. It breaks apart in front of your eyes. You salvage what you can before leaving, and try not to think about the lost crew.

There appear to be a number of small stations nearby. Before you have time to scan them, warnings go off. A Rebel teleporter was used in one of the stations. You've been boarded! They must have a Super Shield bypass unit; boarders are on board!
A transmission from the nearby planet indicates an outpost below which offers supplies to travelers. You send down an away party to check it out.
column12: Drone: DEFENSE 1, REPAIR, DRONE SHIELD, Augment: ION ARMOR, FIRE EXTINGUISHERS, AUTO COOLDOWN, Weapon: LASER BURST 2 A, ION STUN, LASER HULL 1, System: teleporter, mind, hacking,

column11: Your scans reveal a mining base on a nearby planet long since abandoned. No life signs detected.
We understand... Please send help our way if you meet anyone trustworthy.
A small merchant ship messages you, Underground Federation comm channels are all talking about your 'secret' mission. Let us install a weapon to help. Good luck!

A refugee ship fleeing the Rebel advance enters the system. It seems surprised to see you stranded, and admits it was following you from afar in the hopes of you leading it to Federation space. While it doesn't have much fuel to spare, it recognizes you are part of the Federation and offers to split its remaining fuel with you.
You've entered a poorly charted area of space that's known to be home to the Mantis. Ensure your hull plating is up to scratch and that you have enough fuel in the tank to make it through.
Take this bit of scrap as a down-payment. We'll use your jump signatures to follow you. You're really helping us out here. Added a quest marker to your map!
